 High School, and Arata is finally able to leave the island after getting his permission form signed.\n}}\n|}\n\n==''LBX: Little Battlers eXperience''==\n\n===Season 1===\n'''Ending theme'''\n* \"Battle On\" by Mike Twining & Andrew Twining \n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:70%; margin:left; background:#FFF;\"\n|- style=\"border-bottom: 3px solid #CCF\"\n! style=\"width:3em;\"  | No.\n! style=\"width:12em;\" | Dub Title\n! style=\"width:12em;\" | Original U.S. airdate\n|-\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 01\n| Title           = Starting Small\n| AltDate         = August 24, 2014<ref name=\"TV Guide\">{{cite web | url = http://www.tvguide.com/tvshows/lbx/episodes-season-1/683506/ | title=LBX Season 1 Episodes | publisher = TV Guide | accessdate = August 24, 2014}}</ref>\n| ShortSummary    = Van Yamano and his best friends Amy Cohen and Kaz Walker have just entered the Artemis Tournament with the objective to become the best LBX players in the world. After pulling off a huge first round upset Van thinks back to how LBX cost his father his life, or so he believes, how LBX makes him feel closer to his father, and how a mysterious LBX named Achilles first came into his life and set him off on a path he would have never expected. Episode 1 of Danball Senki.\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 02\n| Title           = The Hunt Begins\n| AltDate         = August 31, 2014<ref name=\"TV Guide\"/>\n| ShortSummary    = Van's mom shocks everyone when she says she has moved on and Van can play LBX. Van takes the AX-00 to a local shop where he is offered the Achilles armor. Unfortunately a gang led by Hans Gordon, known as the Hands of Han, has used a fake purchase card to gain the Achilles armor. Van and Amy plot a way to get it back, but in order to do so they must defeat everyone in the gang. Meanwhile Damon Osgood is revealed to have produced the Achilles armor. He is shocked when armor outlines for another new LBX arrive that's sole purpose is to assist Achilles. Episode 2 of Danball Senki.\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 03\n| Title           = Enter the Destroyer\n| AltDate         = September 7, 2014<ref name=\"TV Guide\"/>\n| ShortSummary    = Van is given the Achilles armor and allowed to put it on AX-00. However he is warned in advance that if he losses, AX-00 will become one of Damon's many LBX's. Van, Amy, and Kaz come up with a plan to attack Han's Destroyer. Amy will use Kunoichi's speed to distract Damon, Kaz will attack long range, and Van will swoop in whenever there is a chance. At first the plan seems to be working, but Destroyer unleashes his energy attack to cause a smoke screen. He follows this up by destroying Kaz's Trooper and severely damaging Kunoichi and Achilles. After using the energy attack one too many times Kaz realizes Destroyer's weakness, but when Van and Achilles left by themselves one must wonder can they hand Achilles his first loss or will they suffer a humiliating defeat. Contains content from episodes 3 & 4 of Danball Senki.\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 04\n| Title           = Revelations\n| AltDate         = September 14, 2014<ref name=\"TV Guide\"/>\n| ShortSummary    = After lamenting the loss of Trooper, Kaz is tricked by the Agents into using the LBX Pharaoh, an LBX which hypnotizes Kaz into having one objection: destroy Achilles at all costs. Before Achilles can be destroyed though, a special mode known as V Mode unlocks giving Achilles more strength and power than ever before. The only problem is that V Mode also sends Achilles into a rampage. After the battle Kaz is returned to normal. A day later Tyler Osgood and Len Hiyama approach the kids to discuss Van's LBX and they reveal a shocker- Van's father is still alive and is being held hostage by the organization the New Dawn Raisers. Kaz receives a new LBX to help Van participate in the upcoming Catacombs Challenge. Contains events from episodes 4 (battle with Egypt), 5 (receiving Hunter) & 7 (revelation Profe