, but they get intercepted on the first floor forcing Ban and an injured Master Otaku to support Laura. Laura is defeated, but Van and Master Otaku make it in time to save her LBX and prepare for Round 2 with Amy. Contains scenes from episodes 6 and 7 of Danball Senki W.\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 33\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 7\n| Title           = Plan of Attack\n| AltDate         = November 22, 2015<ref name=\"TV Guide2\"/>\n| ShortSummary    = Amy battles Van and Otacross in a winner takes all slugfest. Amy's speed seems to be too much for Van and Otacross to handle until Perfect ZX-3 throws out an arm and makes contact with the Pandora, stunning Amy. Back-to-back finishing moves destroy the LBX's and free Amy, causing her to collapse. Van installs the vaccine program. We learn the LBX's the others were fighting were brainjacked as they shut down when the vaccine program finishes installing. Amy comes to and admits she does not remember anything after Pandora was destroyed. Amy wants to stay and help free Kaz, but a severe headache hits her and keeps her from joining NICS at this time. The team takes Amy back to Japan where she is placed in protective custody with CIO. Tyler joins the group and announces he'll be joining them from here on out, but he also brings with him a surprise. Nils joins the team. We learn Tyler was forced out of his company and wants to investigate Crystar Ingram and the International LBX Association behind the scenes, but first they decide to analyze the new data they received from Shangpei. The kids are released for some free time, and Nils tells the others how Justin saved his life, leading them to become friends. Elsewhere Prime Minister Vanguard recruits Aaron's team to prepare for the Xirectors next attack. NICS comes to the conclusion that the International LBX Association needs to be investigated, but just before the group lands in L City a new brain jacking occurs, forcing the team to divide into two. Contains scenes from episodes 8 and 9 of Danball Senki W.\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 34\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 8\n| Title           = In Plain Sight\n| AltDate         = November 29, 2015<ref name=\"TV Guide2\"/>\n| ShortSummary    = Van, Justin, Nils, and Tyler begin investigating the International LBX Association,  but little do they know they're being watched by elite fighters who will do anything to stop them from learning the companies secrets. Curt intercepts Nil and forces him to battle. Justin and Van make it to the halls where their air vents are located, but Van gets trapped in the bathroom and has to alter the infiltration route. Van and Justin close in on the control room, but government officials show up and force them to vacate their hiding places. They accounce that the ILBXA is being locked down forcing everyone to leave the premises, stopping the fight between Nil and Curt in the price. Before they leave L City Allen Worthen, President of the ILBXA calls Tyler and invites them to complete their investigation. Instead of finding the master computer they find an assembly line. Seeing no other choice the group returns to NICS where it's announced the Xirectors next target will be at the President's 1 year speech on Aloha Island, taking place at the same time as the next Artemis Tournament. Van, Justin, and Nil have already qualified, so the group starts  working on getting the others qualified. Contains scenes from episodes 9, 11, and 12 of Danball Senki W.\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 35\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 9\n| Title           = Artemis, Round One!\n| AltDate         = December 6, 2015<ref name=\"TV Guide2\"/>\n| ShortSummary    = After Pres. Claudia Denton refuses to reschedule her speech, the team heads for Aloha Island and the Artemis Tournament. Shortly after arriving they run into Hans and Dak and tell them everything. Hans and Dak agree to join the search. The next morning the teams are formed. Van, Justin, and Jessica form one team while 