 December 20, 2015<ref name=\"TV Guide2\"/>\n| ShortSummary    = Van and Hiro get ambushed at the 850m mark, but they are saved by Achilles Deed. Meanwhile Hans and Dak realize Chameleon is running on an auto program and come up with an attack plan for the win. Jackal decides to retreat, but before he can leave Asuka intercepts him and beats him in a battle allowing NICS to arrive and take Jackal into custody. With the President now safe the group returns to focus on Artemis. Otaku Rangers Z win D Group, and both Van's and Hiro's teams make it to the final of E Block. However confusion arises when both teams end in a draw. Contains scenes from episodes 18 and 19 of Danball Senki W.\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 38\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 12\n| Title           = Artemis Battle Royale!\n| AltDate         = February 28, 2016<ref name=\"TV Guide2\"/>\n| ShortSummary    = The Artemis Finals feature a 6-man battle royale with both Van and Hiro present, but little Asuka is ready to unleash her special move and twist most peoples predictions upside down. Meanwhile Curt is tested by a mysterious man in bandages and his deadly new creation- the Slayer Droid. Contains scenes from episodes 20 and 21 of Danball Senki W.\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 39\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 13\n| Title           = Special Assignment\n| AltDate         = March 6, 2016<ref name=\"TV Guide2\"/>\n| ShortSummary    = Professor Yamano contacts NICA and asks them to send the kids to his hidden lab in Albion. By mere coincidence Hiri's mother also works in Albion. The group arrives in Albion, but before the customizations of the LBX's can begin a beainjacking occurs in Albion. The group splits into 2, but one subway stops because of the commotion in the city leading Hiro, Jessica, and Nils to arrive first. Before they can make it to the control computer Curt intercepts them and forces them into battle. Meanwhile on the roof Achilles Fiend is watching, but it gets attached by a Slayer D