pts to assist Van. The mysterious man returns and gives Ban a D-Chip Hologram to battle Achilles Deed in so people can escape. Odin and Perseus are unable to match Achilles Deed's speed, and Odin misses hitting Achilles Fiend with Gungir Blast. Achilles Deed retaliates using his finisher, Dark Storm. He destroys Odin and escapes the D-Chip Hologram. After the battle the mysterious man reveals a new enemy has arisen. Before he can tell Ban and Tyler any more info a man comes on the electronic screen and claims a new group known as The Directors will become the rulers of the Earth, and they will do so by any means necessary. Episode 1 of Danball Senki W.\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 28\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 2\n| Title           = Double Offense\n| AltDate         = October 18, 2015<ref name=\"TV Guide2\"/>\n| ShortSummary    = The mysterious man introduces himself as Cobra. He was sent by Professor Yamano to give Hiro and Van their new LBX's and to stop the threat of the Directors should it arise. He reveals that the Directors are kidnapping the strongest LBX players for unknown reasons. Cobra gives Van a new LBX, Elysion, with which to fight. Van assembles Elysion and Cobra traces down that the hacked computer being controlled by the Directors is the old CIO base. Tyler provides Van and Hiro knowledge on how to get to the base. On B8 the two get ambushed by 5 Inbit's (LBX's that are security guards in the original series but that aren't shown in the dub), but Van and Hiro use good teamwork to stop them and defeat them with ease. The group makes it inside the CIO base where they have to face multiple LBX's. The final set of LBX's in the battle feature two G-Lexes and Achilles Fiend. If they can defeat them they can shut down the hijacked computer. Another mysterious youth shows up and uses a very customized Dequoo to destroy the two G-Lexes. Achilles Fiend retreats and Elysion shuts down the computer. As Van goes to thank the mysterious youth the youth reveals he is not there to help. Instead he is there to defeat Van, and he'll defeat all enemies in they way to make sure they cannot defeat Van before he does. The youth introduces himself as Curt Bryat, but before he can battle Van he senses Tyler and Cobra coming and decides to flee. Over at the Senate Devin is brought out of the shadows and asked to investigate the Detectors. Over across the sea the president of the AU asks her defense secretary and vice president to do research on the LBX crisis. The vice president chooses to go to ILBXF for advice while the defense secretary contacts the Mo's. Contains scenes from episodes 2 and 3 of Danball Senki W.\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 29\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 3\n| Title           = Three's a Crowd\n| AltDate         = October 25, 2015<ref name=\"TV Guide2\"/>\n| ShortSummary    = Tyler and Cobra arrive at the base, but Curt has left. Tyler decides to restore the CIO and contacts Reyna to come to assemble the old base. Cobra reveals all he knows about the detectors, which is not much more than has been shared. He reveals that the LBX's are being taken over through a process called brainjacking. The brainjacking occurs through the M Chip which the ILBXF requires all LBX's to have. However Professor Yamano has ignored that requirement and made it so Perseus and Elysion do not have the M Chip. He also reveals that a third LBX from Professor Yamano will be presented to the winner of the Shibuya Town Martial Arts tournament that afternoon. Over in Shibuya Laura Hansaki wins the martial arts tournament and is presented Minerva. After the tourney she goes to fight her friend Yuki outside when Director LBX's arrive. Minerva and Warrior are able to handle most of them, but then Warrior gets brainjacked. Minerva is forced to take out Warrior and then gets surrounded by Achilles Fiend, a black Kunoichi, and a black Hunter. Van and Hiro arrive and help Laura take out the Kunoichi and Hunter, but Achilles Fiend escapes. Heather is made a member of the team and is taken to the CIO base.  Back at the CIO base Tyler contacts Devin and the Mo's and asks him to investigate the ILBXF. He also tells him he is bringing back the CIO to fight. The Xtroler's for Amy and Kaz are detected.  They appear to be on a plane headed to the AU, but before precise coordinates can be located the signals are cut off. Van and company decide to head to the AU to investigate. That evening Laura, Hiro, and Van acquire permission to go to the AU and search for Kaz and Amy. Contains scenes from episodes 3 and 4 of Danball Senki W.\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 30\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 4\n| Title           = On the Move\n| AltDate         = November 1, 2015<ref name=\"TV Guide2\"/>\n| ShortSummary    = Van, Hiro, Laura, and Cobra are sent to the NICU in Apple City to gain the technology needed to allow their LBX to stop brain jacking. Along the way their plane gets highjacked, and the only way to keep from crashing is to defeat the LBX responsible in head-to-head battles without damaging the plane. Even if they make it, the team will never be the same when Jessica is awaiting them for a showdown. Contains scenes from episodes 4 and 5 of Danball Senki W.\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 31\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 5\n| Title           = Trained Heroes\n| AltDate         = November 8, 2015<ref name=\"TV Guide2\"/>\n| ShortSummary    = The team is divided in two to track down the brainjacked closer. Hiro and Jessica track it to a subway car only to encounter a brainjacked human fighter. As if that weren't enough the subway car restarts and heads for a collision with another car. An unknown LBX, controlled by Justin,  manages to stop it. The team is introduced to Mongoose, and Justin joins the team to stop the brainjacking. Contains scenes from episodes 5 and 6 of Danball Senki W.\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 32\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 6\n| Title           = Shangpei Showdown\n| AltDate         