ed out of his company and wants to investigate Crystar Ingram and the International LBX Association behind the scenes, but first they decide to analyze the new data they received from Shangpei. The kids are released for some free time, and Nils tells the others how Justin saved his life, leading them to become friends. Elsewhere Prime Minister Vanguard recruits Aaron's team to prepare for the Xirectors next attack. NICS comes to the conclusion that the International LBX Association needs to be investigated, but just before the group lands in L City a new brain jacking occurs, forcing the team to divide into two. Contains scenes from episodes 8 and 9 of Danball Senki W.\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 34\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 8\n| Title           = In Plain Sight\n| AltDate         = November 29, 2015<ref name=\"TV Guide2\"/>\n| ShortSummary    = Van, Justin, Nils, and Tyler begin investigating the International LBX Association,  but little do they know they're being watched by elite fighters who will do anything to stop them from learning the companies secrets. Curt intercepts Nil and forces him to battle. Justin and Van make it to the halls where their air vents are located, but Van gets trapped in the bathroom and has to alter the infiltration route. Van and Justin close in on the control room, but government officials show up and force them to vacate their hiding places. They accounce that the ILBXA is being locked down forcing everyone to leave the premises, stopping the fight between Nil and Curt in the price. Before they leave L City Allen Worthen, President of the ILBXA calls Tyler and invites them to complete their investigation. Instead of finding the master computer they find an assembly line. Seeing no other choice the group returns to NICS where it's announced the Xirectors next target will be at the President's 1 year speech on Aloha Island, taking place at the same time as the next Artemis Tournament. Van, Justin, and Nil have already qualified, so the group starts  working on getting the others qualified. Contains scenes from episodes 9, 11, and 12 of Danball Senki W.\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 35\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 9\n| Title           = Artemis, Round One!\n| AltDate         = December 6, 2015<ref name=\"TV Guide2\"/>\n| ShortSummary    = After Pres. Claudia Denton refuses to reschedule her speech, the team heads for Aloha Island and the Artemis Tournament. Shortly after arriving they run into Hans and Dak and tell them everything. Hans and Dak agree to join the search. The next morning the teams are formed. Van, Justin, and Jessica form one team while Hiro, Nil, and Laura form the other. At registration they meet a young warrior named Asuka Carter. Asuka accuses Van of stealing her Xtroller before Jessica notices where it is. Asuka attaches herself to Van and company. Finally the tournament begins, and a huge shock occurs as Asuka wins Block A as a solo fighter without using a single special move. Episode 16 of Danball Senki W.\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 36\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 10\n| Title           = I Spy With My Little Eye\n| AltDate         = December 13, 2015<ref name=\"TV Guide2\"/>\n| ShortSummary    = B Block's final is shown as the Alexander Sisters, South America's LBX champs, use their speed and weapons to advance to the final with ease. C-Block begins, and we see Hans and Dak advance to the final with ease. In the final they meet up with the Jackal and his LBX Chameleon. Hans and Dak rush head in and try to eliminate Chameleon, but Chameleon is persistent and continues to dodge every attack. Van and the others search the stadium for mysterious EM waves but do not find any until the President's speech begins. When the President begins her speech, EM wave readings appear all around the stadium. Jackal switches Mad Dog to auto combat mode and then uses his CCM to activate Router LBX's that have been placed across the ocean. Otacross finds the water readings, so Van and Hiro board their surf sleds to go and investigate the router at 800m. They manage to take out the Router LBX's at 800m, but a second reading pops up at 850m. Meanwhile Asuka gets bored with the C-Block finals but realizes Jackal's controls do not match up with Mad Dog's movements. (S)he uses Vampire Cat's camera mode to zoom in and sees that Jackal is the assassin and that the President is about to get shot unless (s)he finds someway to act. Contains scenes from episodes 17 and 18 of Danball Senki W.\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 37\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 11\n| Title           = Artemis Showdown!\n| AltDate         = December 20, 2015<ref name=\"TV Guide2\"/>\n| ShortSummary    = Van and Hiro get ambushed at the 850m mark, but they are saved by Achilles Deed. Meanwhile Hans and Dak realize Chameleon is running on an auto program and come up with an attack plan for the win. Jackal decides to retreat, but before he can leave Asuka intercepts him and beats him in a battle allowing NICS to arrive and take Jackal into custody. With the President now safe the group returns to focus on Artemis. Otaku Rangers Z win D Group, and both Van's and Hiro's teams make it to the final of E Block. However confusion arises when both teams end in a draw. Contains scenes from episodes 18 and 19 of Danball Senki W.\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 38\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 12\n| Title           = Artemis Battle Royale!\n| AltDate         = February 28, 2016<ref name=\"TV Guide2\"/>\n| ShortSummary    = The Artemis Finals feature a 6-man battle royale with both Van and Hiro present, but little Asuka is ready to unleash her special move and twist most peoples predictions upside down. Meanwhile Curt is tested by a mysterious man in bandages and his deadly new creation- the Slayer Droid. Contains scenes from episodes 20 and 21 of Danball Senki W.\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 39\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 13\n| Title           = Special Assignment\n| AltDate       